in config.php there are a number of paths that need to be specified:

       // (absolute) file locations
        $config['site_filestore'] = '/data/terasender/files/';
        $config['site_temp_filestore'] = '/data/terasender/tmp/';
        $config['site_simplesamllocation'] = '/var/www/terasender/simplesaml/';
        $config['log_location'] = '/data/terasender/log/';

Right now, if you omit the trailing '/' in the path, FileSender fails.  Sometimes with an error you can use (like in case of the log dir), sometimes in a less understandable way (like if you omit the / behind the filestore path, it tries to upload and you see a progress bar that just flickers NaN). 

It would be pretty convenient if it didn't matter whether there was a trailing slash or not.

